	"keywords": "Cloud Computing, S3, node.js",
	"description": "To support file uploads in your application, you will have to learn how to send\nfiles from the frontend [https://austingil.com/uploading-files-with-html/] and \nreceive files on the backend [https://austingil.com/file-uploads-in-node/]. \n\nThis tutorial is going to take a step back and explore architectural changes\nthat&#x27;ll help you reduce costs when adding file uploads to your applications.\n\nHere&#x27;s what we&#x27;ll cover:\n 1. What is Object Storage?\n 2. What is S3?\n 3. Start with an Existing Node.js App",
